{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643252","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643252"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:51:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:51:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17990"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17990","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17990"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10704"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114617"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10704","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10704"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17990"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96620"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10053"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24922"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24923"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114617","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114617"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes how AMPK activation increases fatty acid oxidation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Activates acetyl-CoA carboxylase","Inactivates acetyl-CoA carboxylase","Inactivates TBC1D1 protein","Directly activates carnitine palmitoyltransferase 1","Increases malonyl-CoA synthesis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAMPK activation plays a crucial role in cellular energy homeostasis. It increases fatty acid oxidation primarily by \u003Cstrong\u003Einactivating acetyl-CoA carboxylase\u003C/strong\u003E. This enzyme normally converts acetyl-CoA to malonyl-CoA, which inhibits carnitine palmitoyltransferase 1 (CPT-1), the enzyme that facilitates fatty acid transport into mitochondria for oxidation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EActivating acetyl-CoA carboxylase\u003C/strong\u003E would increase malonyl-CoA levels, inhibiting CPT-1 and reducing fatty acid oxidation. \u003Cstrong\u003EInactivating TBC1D1 protein\u003C/strong\u003E primarily affects glucose transport, not fatty acid metabolism. \u003Cstrong\u003EDirectly activating carnitine palmitoyltransferase 1\u003C/strong\u003E does not occur as AMPK acts indirectly via reducing malonyl-CoA levels. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreasing malonyl-CoA synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E would inhibit fatty acid entry into mitochondria.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBy inactivating acetyl-CoA carboxylase, AMPK reduces malonyl-CoA levels, relieving inhibition of CPT-1 and allowing increased fatty acid entry into mitochondria for oxidation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["AMPK activation leads to increased fatty acid oxidation by inactivating acetyl-CoA carboxylase, which reduces malonyl-CoA levels.","Reduced malonyl-CoA relieves inhibition of carnitine palmitoyltransferase 1, allowing fatty acids to enter mitochondria for oxidation.","AMPK serves as a cellular energy sensor that promotes catabolic pathways when energy levels are low."],"references":["Gilbert-Barness E, Barness LA, Farrell PM, editors. Metabolic diseases: foundations of clinical management, genetics, and pathology. IOS Press; 2017.","Lanham-New SA, Macdonald IA, Roche HM, editors. Nutrition and metabolism. John Wiley \u0026 Sons; 2011.","Roche HM, Macdonald IA, Schols AM, Lanham-New SA, editors. Nutrition and metabolism. John Wiley \u0026 Sons; 2024.","Omiecinski CJ, Vanden Heuvel JP, Perdew GH, Peters JM. Xenobiotic metabolism, disposition, and regulation by receptors: from biochemical phenomenon to predictors of major toxicities. Toxicol Sci. 2011 Mar;120 Suppl 1(Suppl 1):S49-75.","Kumar V, Abbas AK, Aster JC, editors. Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science; 2012.","Hall JE. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2021. Chapter 69; pg. 858."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96620"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17990"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96620","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96620"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-18T13:21:11+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-18T13:21:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10704"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114617"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null